response.overview: Imagine, if you will, the very epicentre of a maelstrom from which you have found yourself ensnared within, unable to escape the eye of the storm, waiting in a restless frenzy for the inevitability of your fate to be pummelled and made anew into oblivion. This, my friend, is but a mere allusion to the chaos, power, and raw magnitude of which you are about to experience. This is the sum of humanity’s labour, the fruits of our progression and suffering. But who are we to say? Who is anyone to judge the nature of such a feat? I am afraid there is no answer, other than that of your own experience into this psychological enigma. This is Who’d, and it knows no bounds but your own...
response.title: Who'd
